The paper deals with capacity results for multicasting nested message sets over combination networks, which involves the use of coding schemes and optimization techniques. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of linear superposition coding and block Markov encoding schemes, which are commonly used in Network Information Theory (cs.NI) and Signal Processing (cs.SI) sub-categories. The paper also introduces a graphical representation and proves a lemma, which are related to Graph Theory (cs.DS) and Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-categories.
